                            <comment id="13008310" author="njiang" created="Fri, 18 Mar 2011 03:38:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue is not a critical issue, as I said in the JIRA, there are two ways to workaround it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BTW, Apache CXF doesn&apos;t maintain CXF 2.2.x branch any more, if you still want to use CXF 2.2.x, you may consider to the commercial product supports from FuseSource.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13028901" author="kajkandler@conficio.com" created="Wed, 4 May 2011 19:15:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;HELP: &quot;As a fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-3143&quot; title=&quot;SOAPBindingUtil &amp;#39;leaks&amp;#39; proxy classes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CXF-3143&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CXF-3143&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; SOAPBindingUtil.getProxy uses now thread context classloader.&quot; in the description, but &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-3143&quot; title=&quot;SOAPBindingUtil &amp;#39;leaks&amp;#39; proxy classes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CXF-3143&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CXF-3143&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is not resolved?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So this problem should not exist!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
